profile  leslie c r letter to miss c leslie dated  june  in autobiographical recollections ed tom taylor ticknor  fields boston   st lothians and border yeomanry  httpwwwwalterscottlibedacukbiographychronologyhtml  edinburgh archive – family  cooper robert l d ed  famous scottish freemasons pp – isbn   edinburgh archive – ballantyne brothers  the early editions of marmion use scotts original spelling of practice still used in the usa later editions compiled without scotts oversight usually favour the modern standard british english spelling of practise  hay james  sir walter scott london p  isbn  retrieved  november    httpwwwwalterscottlibedacukbiographypoethtml  scott the poet walterscottlibedacuk  december  retrieved  november    see old mortality on the university of edinburgh walter scott website  see amy witherbee in habeas corpus british imaginations of power in walter scotts old mortality new literary history   – writes by the s conﬂicts between religious dissidents and the stuart crown had given way to a crown policy of seizing and imprisoning opponents without recourse to the courts in  this policy of using extrajudicial imprisonments to quell rebellion ﬁnally provoked the english parliament to pass the act of habeas corpus in england usually translated as “produce the body” habeas corpus could be invoked by any subject to require that the king or his agents produce the body of a prisoner for adjudication before the courts in its barest terms the great writ protected a subject from indeﬁnite terms of imprisonment from imprisonment outside the kingdom or from imprisonment without cause it did so by asserting the jurisdiction of the courts as superior to the executive powers of the king the act was thus part of a long debate within the three kingdoms about the relationship of king to law and vice versa  witherbee  pp – habeas corpus had been suspended in the mids at the time of the french revolution by william pitt who had called the french declaration of human rights monstrous widely publicised trials for sedition took place in edinburgh  and in london  john thelwall and two others were charged with treason the scottish defendants received harsh sentences whereas the english ones were acquitted according to historian anne stott the difference between the english and scottish trials reflects the different legal systems ironically the acquittals made the loyalist case—that england was a country where a man could have a fair trial  a b chronology of walter scotts life walter scott digital archive retrieved  may    the abbot walter scott digital archive retrieved  may  scott had travelled to london in march  to receive his baronetcy   a b walter scott digital archive – chronology walterscottlibedacuk  oct  retrieved  nov    stuart kelly quoted by arnold zwicky in the book of lost books  a b mckinstry sam fletcher marie  the personal account books of sir walter scott the accounting historians journal  – jstor   subscription required  london medical and surgical journal january   edinburgh profile financial hardship  monuments and monumental inscriptions in scotland the grampian society   biographical index of former fellows of the royal society of edinburgh  –  pdf the royal society of edinburgh july  isbn     x   lockhart john gibson  memoirs of the life of sir walter scott bart philadelphia p  retrieved  november    abbotsford house website  scott sir walter grant george  from bannockburn to flodden wallace bruce and the heroes of medieval scotland nashville cumberland p viii isbn    the oxford companion to english literature th edition edited by margaret drabble oxford university press  pp  …it would be difficult to name from among both modern and ancient works many read more widely and with greater pleasure than the historical novels of … walter scott – alessandro manzoni on the historical novel  higgins charlotte  august  scotlands imagemaker sir walter scott invented english legends the guardian london retrieved    g